1. What is Networking?
Networking is the process of connecting two or more devices (computers, servers, IoT devices, mobile devices, sensors, etc.) to communicate and share resources (data, files, internet, printers) using wired or wireless communication.

2. Types of Networks
2.1 Based on Area
Network	Full Form	Coverage	Examples
PAN	Personal Area Network	1â€“10 m	Bluetooth headset
LAN	Local Area Network	Building/office	Home Wi-Fi
MAN	Metropolitan Area Network	City wide	Cable TV network
WAN	Wide Area Network	Country/continent	Internet
2.2 Based on Topology
Topology	Diagram Idea	Pros	Cons
Bus	All devices on single cable	Simple	Cable failure kills network
Star	All devices â†’ Switch	Easy to manage	Switch failure = full downtime
Ring	Circular	Predictable performance	One break affects ring
Mesh	Every device connects to every other	Highly reliable	Expensive
Hybrid	Mix of topologies	Flexible	Complex
Most common in real world: Star + Partial Mesh

